<div class="intro">
<div class="welcome">
Welcome to ECS, the School  of Electronics and Computer Science at the University of Southampton. ECS is one of the world's leading centres for 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20041208102135/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/research/">research</a>, 
<a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20041208102135/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/about/teaching/">teaching</a>, <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20041208102135/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/business/">enterprise and innovation</a> in Electronics, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science.
<div class="sig">Head of School: <a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20041208102135/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/people/wh">Professor Wendy Hall</a></div>
</div>
<div class="headline"><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20041208102135/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/658"><img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20041208102135im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/image.php?id=news_658_img&amp;maxw=200&amp;maxh=150&amp;corners=10&amp;edge=1&amp;checksum=65c7e7cb7b0dbef14b8ce0eceaefaa8f&amp;fn=fn.png" alt="Sir Tim Berners-Lee" border="0" width="200" height="131" class="thumbnail" /></a><h2>Headline News</h2><h3><a href="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20041208102135/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/news/658">Tim Berners-Lee, World Wide Web inventor, to join ECS</a></h3><p>The inventor of the World Wide Web, Sir Tim Berners-Lee, is to take up a Chair of Computer Science at the University of Southampton's School of Electronics and Computer Science.</p><p>He will hold this position alongside his current appointments as Senior Research Scientist at MIT's Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence Laboratory, and Director of the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C).</p><p></p></div></div><div class='rightside'>

